The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 10 February is 38,207 (4,422.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 05 February, there were 1,450 new confirmed cases (167.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 29 January, there were 2,257 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 36% (807 fewer cases).
